R2 Linked with private.alanandnora.com Wordpress
WordPress ‚Üí Cloudflare R2 Media Storage (Secure, Private, Signed URLs)

This site uses Cloudflare R2 as external media storage for WordPress, via the Media Cloud plugin. The system is configured to keep all media fully private while still allowing WordPress to view and edit files using signed URLs.

No media is publicly accessible on the internet.
Uploads are secure, authenticated, and verifiable.

Architecture

WordPress hosted on Hostinger

Cloudflare R2 as S3-compatible object storage

Media Cloud plugin for:

Upload handling

Storage offload

Signed URL delivery

Secure admin access

Status

WordPress site: Healthy

Media Cloud: Active & Verified

R2 Integration: 100% Functional

Authentication: Working (validated by test suite)

Uploads: Stored directly to R2

Security posture: Private storage + signed URL access

Thumbnails in grid: intentionally cloud icon only (by design, for private storage)

Image editing inside WordPress: Works

Frontend image delivery: Uses signed URLs

No public exposure of files

Cloudflare R2 Configuration

Bucket: private-archive

Permissions: Object Read & Write

Access Scope: Scoped to bucket only

Endpoint format:

https://<ACCOUNT_ID>.r2.cloudflarestorage.com


Example used:

https://7503b89d83d64c4c49d7f81bfd7c6948.r2.cloudflarestorage.com


Access Key + Secret Key created as Account API Token

Bucket remains private

Media Cloud Configuration
Provider

Provider: Other S3-Compatible

Bucket: private-archive

Region: US East (N. Virginia)

Custom Endpoint: Cloudflare R2 S3 URL

Path-Style Endpoints: Enabled (recommended)

Upload Handling

Upload Privacy ACL: Private

Upload Images: Enabled

Upload Videos: Enabled

Upload Docs: Enabled

Delete local files (optional choice, currently configurable)

Secure URL Settings

Signed URLs: Enabled

Expiry: configurable (currently short-duration secure access)

This allows:
‚úîÔ∏è Private storage
‚úîÔ∏è Admin access
‚úîÔ∏è Secure frontend delivery

